// Single Responsibility principle 

// Suppose you have a function and a class,any single identity of your Code 
// that should have single responsibility 
// each component is a differnt function 
// each component should have single responsibiklity we should not multiple things in the component


// restaurant menu  responsibilty should be displaying menu only 
// restaurant responsibility should be displaying card 
// it will show cards on the pageXOffset

// header.js will show header of the page 
// we shouldnt do lot of things in a component 

// modularity - you break down the code into  small  small module so that your code can become testableand maintable
// more maintable and more testable 

// if you have a single unit ,you can write test case easily
// if there is a bug inside this code the test case will catch it easily

// you test each small small piece of your code ,whenever you  are testing this restaurant cart ,all the test cases passes it works perfectly
// if you have a very big application ,component are interlinked one inside the another 
// you will get the random bug,you will have to check whole component to see where the bug is coming 
// distributing your code into smaller smaller pieces and keeping in modular ,testable and maintable 


// card is a single unit ,whenever in our application,there is need  to show the card ,we can just reuse it
//if you follow the single responsibility principle ,you get features of reusablility,code becomes maintainable 
// code becomes more testable 


